Using the future value formula, let's determine the value of the dollar investment after a year.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Future value} &=\$1\times(1 + .0067)^{12}
\\[5pt]
&= \$1\times1.0067^{12}
\\[5pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$1.08}
\end{aligned}$$

**Hence, based on our calculation, the value of the investment after a year is $1.08**

Let's now calculate the value of the investment after two years.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Future value} &=\$1\times(1 + .0067)^{24}
\\[5pt]
&= \$1\times1.0067^{24}
\\[5pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$1.17}
\end{aligned}$$

**Therefore, as can be seen in our calculation, the value of the dollar investment after two years is $1.17.**
